name: Shelved
overview: The eclectic staff and patrons in the underfunded Jameson branch of the Metropolitan Public Library deal with the community and each other’s eccentricities.

episodes.name: Jane Eyre FICTION BRO
episodes.overview: Wendy attempts to get the Jameson library new computers while Howard, the transfer librarian from Midtown, arrives to work at the branch.

episodes.name: Things Fall Apart FICTION ACH
episodes.overview: Howard creates a list of fixes for the library which ends in chaos. Wendy starts a new program, causing an embarrassing misunderstanding.

episodes.name: Drag: The Complete Story NONFIC DOO
episodes.overview: Bryce’s objection to a drag queen storytime reader prompts sensitivity training for the staff. Things get awkward between Howard and Sheila.

episodes.name: And Still I Rise FICTION ANG
episodes.overview: Wendy’s Women’s Appreciation Shelf struggles with intersectionality. Bryce erects a Men’s Shelf, while Jaq and Alvin squabble about art.

episodes.name: The Hunger Games FICTION COL
episodes.overview: Howard, Jaq, and Bryce compete in a book push to win a paid day off. Meanwhile, Wendy panics when Unhoused Wendy locks herself in the bathroom.

episodes.name: Moby Dick FICTION MEL
episodes.overview: Jaq finds her fave author’s new book problematic. Bryce visits a patron about a lost book. Wendy downplays the branch to get donations.

episodes.name: Wall and Piece NONFIC BAN
episodes.overview: Wendy oversees a community mural with temperamental artists. Someone from Unhoused Wendy’s past arrives, causing Howard and Jaq to meddle.
